My fireplace gives off no heat, the ashes chill as the wind.<br>
I am freezing, and yet I make no move to close my door.<br>
I sit transfixed at my desk, staring at a piece of parchment.<br>
The parchment has stolen my soul from me.<br>
I look at my soul, a few scrawled out lines in a blue, frosty ink.<br>
I did not write these lines and yet I did.<br>
Where are you now, my soul? Why did you leave me?<br>
There is no answer, save the howl of the wind as it invades my cottage.<br>
The howling of a storm ever-present, unavoidable, this is my reality.<br>
<br>
I am cold, so very cold. Can I stay like this forever?<br>
<br>
In time I close my door. The will to survive is too great.<br>
But I might open it later, at the right time.<br>
And maybe I will be able to light my fire once again,<br>
using this parchment as kindling.  <p><IMG SRC=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/61/3198661.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#5F9EA0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usasi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sasi</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://a1060.g.akamai.net/f/1060/597/30minutes/www.zing.com/picture/pad9e25fb1e1af65a8eddd5c924e825d5/feadd13d.gif height=25 width=20 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Genial Dictator</span><br> <font color=#000000>(5/8/01 7:14:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/fthemissednotethestage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Poem in Celebration of Velious</span><hr size=1> Excellent!  <br>
